      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:1:9",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِنِّي لَأَكْرَهُ لِلرَّجُلِ أَنْ يَكُونَ عَلَيْهِ نِعْمَةٌ مِنَ اللَّهِ فَلَا يُظْهِرَهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, form Ibn Abu Umeyr, raising it, said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘I<sup>asws</sup> dislike it for the man that a Bounty happens to be upon him from Allah<sup>azwj</sup>, so he does not manifest it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr in a marfu‘ manner has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘I dislike to see a man who has received a bounty from Allah but does not show it.\" "
        ]
      }
    },
